# --- dtoa.cyr ---

# dtoa.cyr — round-trip-correct f64 <-> decimal conversion for bayan.
# Usage: included by the json profile. Requires: alloc.cyr, string.cyr.
#
# WHY: the old path formatted every f64 as fmt_float_buf(v, buf, 6) — a fixed
# 6-decimal cap that (a) loses ~9 mantissa bits on values like 1/3, (b) flushes
# |x|<5e-7 to 0, and (c) overflowed i64 on |x|>=2^63 / Inf / NaN, emitting the
# NON-JSON token "-.00000-". Parsing used two divergent, both-imprecise atofs
# that disagreed by 1 ULP on identical text, and the exponent apply looped once
# per unit of the exponent VALUE — an algorithmic-complexity DoS.
#
# Replaces all of that:
#   bayan_f64_to_json(bits, buf) — Grisu2 (Loitsch; the miloyip/rapidjson port):
#     integer-only, ALWAYS succeeds (no Dragon4 fallback), output is guaranteed
#     to round-trip and is shortest-or-near-shortest. Non-finite -> "null".
#   bayan_f64_from_json(cstr) — Clinger fast path (exact single-rounding) + a
#     normalized-DiyFp path via the SAME cached-power table, exponent clamped
#     during scanning (no DoS).
# CHANGELOG bayan [1.2.1]; folded into cyrius CHANGELOG [6.4.69].

